WEBVTT



00:00:13.451 --> 00:00:15.078
How's your condition?

00:00:18.832 --> 00:00:20.875
So, as always,

00:00:21.376 --> 00:00:23.670
your opponent has no idea about this.

00:00:23.753 --> 00:00:25.672
He will come at you with full force.

00:00:25.755 --> 00:00:28.508
Make sure you don't get caught.

00:00:28.591 --> 00:00:30.552
The match is starting soon.

00:00:31.052 --> 00:00:32.512
Can we give this a rest?

00:00:35.014 --> 00:00:37.392
A loser dog acting all mighty, huh?

00:00:44.232 --> 00:00:45.567
I'm counting on you, okay?

00:00:54.909 --> 00:00:56.786
That damn bastard.

00:01:25.106 --> 00:01:27.400
Good! Let's go!

00:01:35.825 --> 00:01:37.911
We've got more power.

00:01:37.994 --> 00:01:41.039
Give it your all. Put your soul into it!

00:01:41.539 --> 00:01:43.708
Soul? That's so old-fashioned.

00:01:49.005 --> 00:01:50.590
Do your best!

00:02:06.481 --> 00:02:07.941
I trust you.

00:02:08.024 --> 00:02:09.442
Do a good job, okay?

00:02:12.820 --> 00:02:15.156
A loser dog acting all mighty, huh?

00:02:23.748 --> 00:02:25.250
Johan!

00:02:26.042 --> 00:02:27.710
Johan, you did well!

00:02:29.587 --> 00:02:32.632
Good job! That was amazing!

00:02:32.715 --> 00:02:36.552
You know what'll happen
if you betray me, don't you?

00:02:47.272 --> 00:02:52.694
Johan, what are you doing?!
Finish him already!

00:03:00.451 --> 00:03:02.245
Move in, Johan!

00:03:20.430 --> 00:03:21.764
What's with that guy?

00:03:24.225 --> 00:03:26.019
Does he want to end up like me?

00:03:37.572 --> 00:03:39.699
Don't run, Hwang Johan!

00:04:12.565 --> 00:04:15.109
-I found myself cheering for him.
-Yeah.

00:04:27.997 --> 00:04:29.749
Learn how to box!

00:04:29.832 --> 00:04:31.918
-Go back to Korea!
-What?

00:04:32.627 --> 00:04:34.754
Get out of the ring!

00:04:37.382 --> 00:04:38.800
Shut up.

00:04:38.883 --> 00:04:39.926
What did you say?

00:04:40.009 --> 00:04:41.636
-Come here, you bastard!
-Huh? Sumiko?

00:04:41.719 --> 00:04:45.598
-Hey, calm down!
-Who the hell are you? Don't get cocky!

00:04:45.681 --> 00:04:46.974
Calm down!

00:04:49.685 --> 00:04:53.898
He's just a pitiful guy who doesn't know
a hard worker when he sees one.

00:05:01.406 --> 00:05:02.240
Wait, what?

00:05:03.032 --> 00:05:04.033
Ryu!

00:05:05.451 --> 00:05:06.285
What?

00:05:09.705 --> 00:05:11.165
Wait. Stop!

00:05:17.755 --> 00:05:18.965
-Sumiko!
-Ryu.

00:05:19.048 --> 00:05:20.049
Here.

00:05:20.633 --> 00:05:21.634
Thanks.

00:05:22.510 --> 00:05:24.303
-Here.
-Oh, thank you.

00:05:27.598 --> 00:05:30.476
-Sorry for doing that out of nowhere!
-It's fine.

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:33.438
But wait, do you speak Japanese?

00:05:34.021 --> 00:05:35.898
Yes. That's right.

00:05:36.941 --> 00:05:40.528
I speak six languages.

00:05:41.112 --> 00:05:43.281
Wow, that's incredible.

00:05:44.657 --> 00:05:47.368
My name is Sua. Hwang Sua.

00:05:48.202 --> 00:05:49.078
Hwang?

00:05:49.162 --> 00:05:51.831
Yes. I'm Johan's little sister.

00:05:52.582 --> 00:05:53.875
What is your name?

00:05:53.958 --> 00:05:57.086
I'm Sumiko.

00:05:57.170 --> 00:05:58.671
Oh, Sumiko.

00:05:58.754 --> 00:06:03.217
Thank you so much for helping me, Sumiko.

00:06:03.301 --> 00:06:06.679
Also, I'm sorry.

00:06:07.472 --> 00:06:11.684
When I get angry, I get tunnel vision.

00:06:12.768 --> 00:06:14.770
I'm so sorry.

00:06:14.854 --> 00:06:15.897
It's fine.

00:06:15.980 --> 00:06:18.858
Though, it did catch us by surprise.

00:06:18.941 --> 00:06:21.402
-Right?
-Yeah.

00:06:26.115 --> 00:06:30.453
Could it be that you two are

00:06:30.953 --> 00:06:34.290
my brother's fans?

00:06:45.510 --> 00:06:46.802
Mr. Shim.

00:06:47.303 --> 00:06:50.389
I'm sorry we couldn't deliver results
after being given the chance

00:06:50.473 --> 00:06:52.517
to compete in an international match.

00:06:53.017 --> 00:06:57.063
No, Johan fought with everything he had.

00:06:58.481 --> 00:07:01.108
Could I chat with him alone?

00:07:01.192 --> 00:07:03.903
Oh, yes, go right ahead.

00:07:06.572 --> 00:07:09.867
Make sure you thank him properly.

00:07:11.994 --> 00:07:13.746
Let's go.

00:07:39.480 --> 00:07:42.400
Don't put me on edge like that.

00:07:44.068 --> 00:07:46.654
Who told you
to let it drag out to a decision?

00:07:47.154 --> 00:07:49.156
You just needed to give us a clean loss.

00:07:52.159 --> 00:07:55.496
A knockout. I meant a knockout.

00:07:57.248 --> 00:08:01.043
Well, fine.
As promised, you became a loser dog.

00:08:01.711 --> 00:08:03.588
So I'll keep my promise too.

00:08:22.398 --> 00:08:24.859
It's because you keep reading
this kind of trash.

00:08:35.995 --> 00:08:37.204
See you again.

00:08:53.888 --> 00:08:55.389
Johan!

00:08:57.725 --> 00:09:00.144
Johan! Oh, no!

00:09:00.227 --> 00:09:02.980
Are you okay? That looks painful.

00:09:04.482 --> 00:09:05.358
Huh?

00:09:05.441 --> 00:09:06.901
Hmm? Oh!

00:09:07.610 --> 00:09:09.153
Good work.

00:09:11.822 --> 00:09:13.199
Why's that guy here?

00:09:16.661 --> 00:09:19.830
These two were really cheering you on.

00:09:20.706 --> 00:09:21.999
Isn't that right?

00:09:22.083 --> 00:09:25.461
Uh, sorry, I don't know any Korean.

00:09:25.544 --> 00:09:28.005
Oh, that's right.

00:09:28.673 --> 00:09:29.548
Huh?

00:09:30.257 --> 00:09:33.260
You're friends with Johan,
aren't you, Ryu?

00:09:33.886 --> 00:09:35.262
Friends?

00:09:35.346 --> 00:09:37.223
Wait, no. I didn't say anything.

00:09:37.723 --> 00:09:39.934
What? Don't be shy!

00:09:40.434 --> 00:09:41.644
Oh, Johan.

00:09:42.144 --> 00:09:48.818
Ryu asked me how to say
"Good work" in Korean before you got here.

00:09:48.901 --> 00:09:53.864
Oh, my gosh! I'm so jealous.
You have such a nice friend.

00:09:54.365 --> 00:09:57.326
I'm gonna hang out with Sumiko.

00:09:57.410 --> 00:09:58.619
Move over.

00:09:58.703 --> 00:10:00.204
Sumiko, let's go!

00:10:00.287 --> 00:10:02.039
-Huh? Wait--
-Hurry!

00:10:02.123 --> 00:10:03.165
Ryu!

00:10:04.542 --> 00:10:05.626
Oh!

00:10:06.210 --> 00:10:08.546
So, you're the one
who ran from the hospital.

00:10:10.005 --> 00:10:11.507
I didn't run.

00:10:11.590 --> 00:10:12.550
The hospital?

00:10:13.509 --> 00:10:17.555
Thank you so much for saving Ryu.

00:10:19.348 --> 00:10:20.474
It was nothing.

00:10:28.023 --> 00:10:30.776
-What? Did you hurt your hand?
-Nah.

00:10:31.402 --> 00:10:33.529
It's just a bit numb. I'm fine.

00:10:34.029 --> 00:10:38.033
You gotta watch out
for punch-drunk syndrome and stuff.

00:10:38.117 --> 00:10:39.869
Please be more careful!

00:10:39.952 --> 00:10:41.454
You've got some on you again.

00:10:41.537 --> 00:10:43.456
I'm fine. Don't worry.

00:10:43.539 --> 00:10:45.833
I usually take my opponent down
before they hit me.

00:10:45.916 --> 00:10:47.084
Huh?

00:10:48.127 --> 00:10:52.173
Oh, right. You did great, Johan.
You win some, you lose some.

00:10:52.798 --> 00:10:54.049
That's just how it goes.

00:10:54.133 --> 00:10:55.968
-Keep it up!
-Eat your food.

00:10:56.051 --> 00:10:57.470
You two are really close.

00:10:58.471 --> 00:11:00.848
It's always been just the two of us.

00:11:02.308 --> 00:11:03.142
What?

00:11:03.225 --> 00:11:04.977
Don't run your mouth off.

00:11:07.313 --> 00:11:10.316
So, are you two a couple?

00:11:11.108 --> 00:11:12.193
No.

00:11:12.276 --> 00:11:17.031
Ryu is just staying at my place
while he's here on vacation.

00:11:17.907 --> 00:11:21.118
-Oh, is that so?
-It's true.

00:11:21.202 --> 00:11:23.996
We're just childhood friends. Right?

00:11:24.497 --> 00:11:25.623
Yeah.

00:11:25.706 --> 00:11:27.041
"Childhood friends"?

00:11:27.124 --> 00:11:28.876
Yeah. You see…

00:11:28.959 --> 00:11:31.462
I had a lot going on at home.

00:11:31.545 --> 00:11:36.467
So, ever since elementary school,
Ryu's family has done so much for me.

00:11:37.593 --> 00:11:39.345
Since elementary school?

00:11:40.221 --> 00:11:42.223
You've known each other for a long time.

00:11:43.349 --> 00:11:47.019
But what is a "childhood friend"?

00:11:48.562 --> 00:11:51.023
How is it different from being a couple?

00:11:51.106 --> 00:11:52.525
-Hwang Sua.
-Huh?

00:11:52.608 --> 00:11:53.901
That's private.

00:11:54.735 --> 00:11:56.987
I'm so sorry! Oh, I did it again.

00:11:58.239 --> 00:12:02.326
No, it's totally fine.
Let's just forget privacy altogether.

00:12:04.411 --> 00:12:05.454
So heavy…

00:12:07.748 --> 00:12:09.375
He's a lightweight, huh?

00:12:10.334 --> 00:12:12.753
Yeah, but he still drinks.

00:12:17.299 --> 00:12:18.425
Walk properly.

00:12:18.926 --> 00:12:21.637
The church remained largely undamaged.

00:12:21.720 --> 00:12:27.142
As there is still smoke, we advise locals
to keep doors and windows closed.

00:12:27.226 --> 00:12:32.523
Our team found a Molotov cocktail
near the altar while on-site

00:12:32.606 --> 00:12:34.608
that may have caused the fire.

00:12:35.150 --> 00:12:38.320
Meanwhile, a minor has turned himself in
to the police today.

00:12:38.404 --> 00:12:42.408
-The motive remains unclear.
-The culprit was a kid, huh?

00:12:42.491 --> 00:12:43.868
Investigation is ongoing.

00:12:46.745 --> 00:12:51.625
This is amazing, Sumiko.
Did you draw all this yourself?

00:12:51.709 --> 00:12:52.710
Yeah.

00:12:53.752 --> 00:12:56.005
How long have you been in Berlin?

00:12:56.839 --> 00:12:59.717
Well, I guess this is my third year.

00:13:00.718 --> 00:13:05.222
She works part-time
to put herself through fashion college.

00:13:06.056 --> 00:13:09.059
-That's so cool.
-No, not at all.

00:13:09.143 --> 00:13:12.771
I do work part-time,
but I'm also in debt to my dad.

00:13:12.855 --> 00:13:14.356
It's still amazing.

00:13:15.858 --> 00:13:19.403
What about you, Sua?
You're a student, right?

00:13:19.486 --> 00:13:23.073
Yeah. I go to Heidelberg University.

00:13:23.949 --> 00:13:24.950
What?

00:13:25.868 --> 00:13:29.204
Huh? Which department?

00:13:32.499 --> 00:13:35.085
Medical. Is it medicine in Japanese?

00:13:35.169 --> 00:13:38.881
-Wow, that's seriously impressive.
-Amazing!

00:13:38.964 --> 00:13:40.424
Not at all.

00:13:41.550 --> 00:13:45.471
Johan is way more amazing than me.

00:13:47.723 --> 00:13:53.395
Because I happened to be good at studying,
Johan has always supported me.

00:13:54.647 --> 00:13:57.274
He's been working hard to earn money

00:13:57.775 --> 00:14:03.489
and provide me with a good environment.

00:14:04.531 --> 00:14:05.366
I see.

00:14:09.411 --> 00:14:12.122
We don't have parents.

00:14:13.958 --> 00:14:16.543
Johan is my mom and dad.

00:14:16.627 --> 00:14:19.129
He's my entire family.

00:14:21.674 --> 00:14:24.259
If I were ordinary,

00:14:25.719 --> 00:14:30.724
he might not have had to

00:14:31.225 --> 00:14:33.519
push himself so hard.

00:14:38.023 --> 00:14:40.943
I wonder if he is happy.

00:15:14.226 --> 00:15:16.061
-Yo.
-Hey.

00:15:28.282 --> 00:15:29.366
Um…

00:15:30.868 --> 00:15:32.911
Is your hand…

00:15:34.413 --> 00:15:35.414
Oh.

00:15:36.081 --> 00:15:37.374
It's nothing.

00:15:41.837 --> 00:15:45.174
Your match was amazing.

00:15:46.175 --> 00:15:48.802
It was my first time seeing boxing live.

00:15:49.303 --> 00:15:50.637
How do I put this?

00:15:51.680 --> 00:15:52.973
It was moving.

00:15:55.350 --> 00:15:56.560
How?

00:15:57.269 --> 00:16:00.522
Even when you fell, you got back up.

00:16:02.733 --> 00:16:03.734
What?

00:16:04.693 --> 00:16:07.196
Uh, basically…

00:16:08.697 --> 00:16:10.616
The way you never gave up

00:16:11.825 --> 00:16:14.703
made you look stronger than anyone else.

00:16:29.384 --> 00:16:33.222
Why didn't you say anything to the police?

00:16:35.099 --> 00:16:37.226
The one who set the church on fire

00:16:37.309 --> 00:16:39.186
was a kid, right?

00:16:41.814 --> 00:16:43.732
It was on the news earlier.

00:16:49.446 --> 00:16:52.282
The kid had the same eyes

00:16:52.908 --> 00:16:54.159
as me.

00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:56.161
Eyes?

00:16:57.412 --> 00:16:58.956
Hmm.

00:17:03.168 --> 00:17:05.212
When you feel like…

00:17:07.589 --> 00:17:13.345
no one in the world sees you…

00:17:16.431 --> 00:17:18.433
it makes you…

00:17:21.562 --> 00:17:25.023
want to destroy…

00:17:27.526 --> 00:17:28.485
that world.

00:17:37.536 --> 00:17:39.246
What am I even saying?

00:18:28.003 --> 00:18:30.839
NEW MESSAGE FROM SUA

00:18:30.923 --> 00:18:32.549
THANKS TO YOU, I'M HAPPY.

00:18:32.633 --> 00:18:34.885
I'M OKAY NOW.
I'M GLAD YOU MADE A GOOD FRIEND.

00:18:36.303 --> 00:18:37.512
What is she saying?

00:18:53.278 --> 00:18:54.154
Good morning.

00:18:54.238 --> 00:18:55.364
Hey.

00:18:56.281 --> 00:18:57.282
Here.

00:19:03.789 --> 00:19:06.541
What are your plans for today?

00:19:07.834 --> 00:19:09.336
Nothing really.

00:19:12.422 --> 00:19:13.423
Then…

00:19:16.176 --> 00:19:17.427
come with me.

00:19:18.428 --> 00:19:20.597
Huh? Where to?

00:19:23.558 --> 00:19:26.937
I'll show you something interesting.

00:19:28.105 --> 00:19:28.939
What is it?

00:19:32.943 --> 00:19:33.944
The soul.

00:19:35.404 --> 00:19:36.571
The soul?

00:19:40.659 --> 00:19:41.535
Hello?

00:19:41.618 --> 00:19:43.578
Where the hell are you, Johan?

00:19:43.662 --> 00:19:45.706
Sorry, I have some business
to take care of.

00:19:45.789 --> 00:19:49.167
What kind of business
could you have in Germany?

00:19:50.752 --> 00:19:53.422
Whatever. Where are you right now?

00:19:53.505 --> 00:19:56.091
Mr. Shim wants to see you
before heading back to Korea.

00:19:56.174 --> 00:19:59.761
That's perfect.
I have something to discuss with him too.

00:20:00.846 --> 00:20:04.725
You're not gonna say
something unnecessary again, are you?

00:20:05.225 --> 00:20:07.561
-It's something important.
-Hey, you--

00:20:28.582 --> 00:20:29.666
Johan.

00:20:41.970 --> 00:20:43.430
I'm not doing this anymore.

00:20:44.639 --> 00:20:45.640
What?

00:20:49.144 --> 00:20:51.438
I'm saying I'm not gonna do

00:20:52.606 --> 00:20:54.316
these fixed fights anymore.

00:20:54.858 --> 00:20:55.984
Mr. Shim.

00:20:56.693 --> 00:20:57.944
Could it be that you…

00:20:58.028 --> 00:21:00.197
No. I'm just doing my job as a promoter.

00:21:03.617 --> 00:21:04.910
What nonsense is this?

00:21:04.993 --> 00:21:06.286
And also,

00:21:07.204 --> 00:21:09.122
I'm not a loser.

00:21:11.041 --> 00:21:12.959
I'm not a loser dog!

00:21:18.048 --> 00:21:20.008
You bastard. What's your problem?!

00:21:23.387 --> 00:21:24.346
You damn bastard.

00:21:24.429 --> 00:21:25.847
Oh, my bag!

00:21:59.965 --> 00:22:01.800
Yes! I totally did it.

00:22:04.094 --> 00:22:07.556
You're seriously crazy, you know that?

00:22:07.639 --> 00:22:09.516
Wait, I'm not in trouble, am I?

00:22:10.100 --> 00:22:12.436
-I sent that guy flying.
-It's okay.

00:22:12.519 --> 00:22:13.520
I'll be okay, right?

00:22:14.771 --> 00:22:16.273
Up until now,

00:22:17.941 --> 00:22:19.985
I'd been losing matches on purpose.

00:22:21.278 --> 00:22:26.032
Then that man would give me money.

00:22:26.700 --> 00:22:27.701
What?

00:22:28.702 --> 00:22:32.164
-But you…
-Yeah?

00:22:32.247 --> 00:22:33.915
You sent him flying.

00:22:35.667 --> 00:22:36.668
So, now…

00:22:37.878 --> 00:22:39.379
I'm free!

00:22:39.463 --> 00:22:40.714
Freedom!

00:22:48.555 --> 00:22:50.390
To be honest, this injury…

00:22:54.019 --> 00:22:58.482
I got it when I saved you.

00:22:59.316 --> 00:23:00.984
So, it was my fault?

00:23:01.067 --> 00:23:03.153
No, it wasn't.

00:23:04.446 --> 00:23:07.073
It's thanks to you.

00:23:08.783 --> 00:23:09.784
This…

00:23:12.287 --> 00:23:13.955
This is the mark of freedom.

00:23:18.126 --> 00:23:19.878
Can you survive from now on?

00:23:22.172 --> 00:23:25.383
I was already dead.

00:23:56.498 --> 00:23:58.416
I used to read this.

00:24:01.753 --> 00:24:03.547
It's a masterpiece.

00:24:05.340 --> 00:24:07.342
Is this how you learned Japanese?

00:24:14.349 --> 00:24:16.685
I've read this many times.

00:24:16.768 --> 00:24:18.103
Over and over.

00:24:21.523 --> 00:24:25.694
Because I wanted to understand

00:24:27.612 --> 00:24:30.532
the meaning behind the story.

00:24:31.866 --> 00:24:33.159
Impressive.

00:24:34.578 --> 00:24:35.704
Impressive, right?

00:24:36.204 --> 00:24:37.122
Yeah.

00:24:48.133 --> 00:24:50.802
What will you do now?

00:24:55.307 --> 00:24:58.184
I'll go back to Korea.

00:25:00.645 --> 00:25:01.896
I see.

00:25:02.564 --> 00:25:03.773
And after that?

00:25:09.487 --> 00:25:10.989
After that?

00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:15.035
How would I know?

00:25:17.287 --> 00:25:18.330
Right.

00:25:20.415 --> 00:25:22.042
From here on out…

00:25:25.420 --> 00:25:27.047
it's my story.

00:25:39.768 --> 00:25:40.769
Huh?

00:26:28.274 --> 00:26:29.401
What about you?

00:26:29.901 --> 00:26:30.902
Me?

00:26:33.738 --> 00:26:34.948
Are you

00:26:36.324 --> 00:26:38.785
still gonna stay here?

00:26:43.748 --> 00:26:46.543
I'll head back too.

00:26:50.755 --> 00:26:54.300
I've decided to go back.

00:26:58.555 --> 00:26:59.556
I see.

00:27:00.974 --> 00:27:01.975
Yeah.

00:27:05.979 --> 00:27:07.689
I don't really get it myself.

00:27:09.065 --> 00:27:10.692
But watching you,

00:27:11.443 --> 00:27:16.197
it felt like you won
something more important

00:27:16.281 --> 00:27:18.032
even though you lost the match.

00:27:24.205 --> 00:27:25.206
All this time…

00:27:27.500 --> 00:27:29.002
I've been running away…

00:27:31.921 --> 00:27:34.340
from things I didn't know how to handle.

00:27:36.634 --> 00:27:37.635
But…

00:27:40.638 --> 00:27:41.639
I also…

00:27:43.600 --> 00:27:44.684
Me too.

00:27:52.609 --> 00:27:54.903
I'm just like you.

00:27:56.237 --> 00:27:57.238
What?

00:27:59.199 --> 00:28:02.368
That's why I was at the church.

00:28:05.163 --> 00:28:06.206
Because…

00:28:12.212 --> 00:28:17.967
I was lying to myself.

00:28:21.971 --> 00:28:27.602
Caution. The train is now arriving.

00:28:28.686 --> 00:28:29.687
But…

00:28:31.981 --> 00:28:33.191
I'm not anymore.

00:28:40.198 --> 00:28:41.407
How about you?

00:28:44.077 --> 00:28:45.328
Can you win?

00:28:53.127 --> 00:28:54.254
I'll give it a try.

00:29:07.559 --> 00:29:08.685
Bye, then.

00:29:09.519 --> 00:29:10.520
Bye.

00:29:19.237 --> 00:29:24.576
Hello, welcome aboard
the local train to Schönefeld.

00:29:24.659 --> 00:29:27.328
We will be departing shortly.

00:29:27.412 --> 00:29:32.500
All of us at the German Railway
wish you a pleasant journey.

00:30:25.303 --> 00:30:28.514
JOHAN

00:32:47.361 --> 00:32:50.281
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura